                            <comment id="12678077" author="erikholstad@gmail.com" created="Mon, 2 Mar 2009 20:05:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;  public static BatchUpdate toBatchUpdate(RowResult rr){&lt;br/&gt;
    BatchUpdate bu = new BatchUpdate(rr.getRow());&lt;br/&gt;
    for(Map.Entry&amp;lt;byte[], Cell&amp;gt; entry : rr.entrySet())&lt;/p&gt;
{
      bu.put(entry.getKey(), entry.getValue().getValue());
    }
&lt;p&gt;    return bu;&lt;br/&gt;
  }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is the code that I propose as a util method, not really sure if it is&lt;br/&gt;
the best way of doing it and where to put it, that is why I didn&apos;t  patch&lt;br/&gt;
it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Erik&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678095" author="streamy" created="Mon, 2 Mar 2009 20:32:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think there should be a new constructor in BatchUpdate and a new constructor in RowResult.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; BatchUpdate(RowResult rr) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// conversion code that instantiates a &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; BatchUpdate with values in passed RowResult
&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; RowResult(BatchUpdate bu) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// conversion code that instantiates a &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; RowResult with values in passed BatchUpdate
&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678099" author="erikholstad@gmail.com" created="Mon, 2 Mar 2009 20:36:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not really sure what it would mean to go from a BU to a RR, but I also think&lt;br/&gt;
that it would be good to put the functionality into a new constructor. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678102" author="streamy" created="Mon, 2 Mar 2009 20:46:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;no idea if there&apos;s a use case for that.  issue is just for RR -&amp;gt; BU so just leave it out.  can be done in the future if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678421" author="stack" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 19:29:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on new BU constructor that takes a RR&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679328" author="erikholstad@gmail.com" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 19:59:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Small patch with a new constructor for BatchUpdate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679339" author="streamy" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 20:29:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch for 0.19.1 and 0.20.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679341" author="streamy" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 20:31:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Side note, this may change even prior to 880 because of changes coming out of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1234&quot; title=&quot;Change HBase StoreKey format&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1234&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1234&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
